### 0. System Constraints (Enforced)

*   **Scoring Anchor:** Existing human baseline solutions (170GHz Gyrotrons for ECRH) exhibit an overall efficiency of ~35–45% and a CW lifetime of ~500 hours, defined as the **60-point standard**. This roadmap targets a **90-point production-ready level**: **Overall efficiency ≥ 50%** and **CW lifetime ≥ 2000 hours**.
*   **Material Doctrine:** Mandatory use of **Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS)** industrial standards (OFHC copper cavities, sapphire/diamond output windows, SmCo permanent magnets/copper coils, oxygen-free copper cooling structures). Prohibited from specifying single suppliers.
*   **Implementation Preference:** **Robustness over peak performance.** Designs must be rugged with ±10% process tolerance and redundant cooling.
*   **Expression Rules:** Strip all fluff. Retain only physical parameters, quantitative thresholds, and failure modes.

