### 1. Pain Points Definition (Why)

Existing 60-point solutions face critical failure modes:

*   **Poor Electron Gun Laminarity:** The annular electron beam exhibits high velocity spread (Δv/v > 8%), limiting beam-wave interaction efficiency to <60%. Non-uniform cathode emission causes local overheating, restricting lifetime.
*   **Excessive Cavity Ohmic Losses:** Conventional copper cavities have high surface resistance (~0.01 Ω/□ at 170GHz), with ohmic losses accounting for >25% of input power, capping overall efficiency.
*   **Output Window Thermal Stress Failure:** Sapphire windows (Al₂O₃, thermal conductivity ~30 W/m·K) suffer center temperature rises >200°C under CW operation, exceeding the fracture threshold (~300 MPa).
*   **Magnet System Redundancy:** Traditional water-cooled electromagnetic coils consume >50 kW and weigh >5 tons, hindering integration into compact fusion devices.

