### 2. Breakthrough Solution (What)

**Core Architecture:**
Laminar flow electron gun + Diamond output window + Gradient-doped resonant cavity + Permanent magnet packaged system.

**Counter-Consensus Point:** Abandoning the "Electromagnet + Copper Cavity + Sapphire Window" legacy design in favor of a **"Permanent Magnet Circuit + Diamond Window + Gradient-Doped Cavity"** to achieve simultaneous leaps in efficiency and lifetime.

**Parameter Benchmark:**

| Metric | Human Baseline (60 pts) | Proposed Optimum (90 pts) |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Overall Efficiency (DC-to-RF)** | 35–45% | **≥ 50%** |
| **CW Lifetime** | ~500 hours | **≥ 2000 hours** |
| **Output Power** | ~1 MW (Pulsed) | **≥ 1 MW (CW)** |
| **Frequency Stability** | ±0.5% | **± 0.1%** |
| **Electron Beam Velocity Spread** | Δv/v > 8% | **Δv/v < 5%** |

**Supply Chain Anchoring:**
*   **Resonant Cavity / Electron Gun:** ASTM F68 OFHC Copper or ASTM B387 Grade 361 Molybdenum. Surface roughness Ra < 0.05 μm. Thermal conductivity > 400 W/m·K. Gradient doping concentration slope ≤ 10¹⁸ cm⁻³/μm.
*   **Output Window:** Single-crystal diamond (Thermal cond. > 2000 W/m·K, ε_r ≈ 5.7 @ 170GHz) or Sapphire (ε_r ≈ 9.3, >30 W/m·K). Diameter ≥ 50 mm, thickness tolerance ±0.01 mm.
*   **Magnet System:** Sm₂Co₁₇ Permanent Magnets (Br ≥ 1.1T, Hcj ≥ 2000 kA/m) or water-cooled copper coils (current density ≤ 10 A/mm²). Field uniformity ±1% in cavity region.
*   **Cooling Structure:** OFHC copper micro-channel heat sinks (channel width ≤ 0.5 mm, flow rate ≥ 2 m/s). Thermal resistance < 0.1 °C/W.

