### 3. Implementation Roadmap (How)

#### Step A: Laminar Gun & Gradient-Doped Cavity Prototyping
*   **Action:** Design a coaxial double-anode electron gun optimizing electrode shape to achieve Δv/v < 5%. Implement gradient doping on the cavity inner wall (surface high-conductivity Cu + inner high-strength Cu) to reduce ohmic loss.
*   **Acceptance Criteria:** Electron trajectory deviation < 0.1 mm. Cavity Q-factor > 10⁴. Small-signal gain > 30 dB.

#### Step B: Diamond Window & Permanent Magnet Validation
*   **Action:** Integrate a single-crystal diamond window (with Ti/Au transition layers). Implement a SmCo permanent magnet circuit (Axial B ≤ 2T). Test window temperature rise under CW power.
*   **Acceptance Criteria:** Window thermal stress < 200 MPa. Magnetic field uniformity ±1%. Window transmission loss < 0.5 dB.

#### Step C: Full-scale MW CW System & Lifetime Qualification
*   **Action:** Assemble the full system. Conduct 2000-hour CW aging tests. Monitor efficiency decay (<5%) and power fluctuation (±2%).
*   **Acceptance Criteria:** Overall efficiency ≥ 50%. Output power ≥ 1 MW CW. Lifetime ≥ 2000 hours.

